Cook the quinoa: In a #small pot{}, bring @water{1 1/2%cups}, the @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and a large pinch of @salt{pinch} to a boil. Once boiling, add the @red quinoa{3/4%cup}. Cover and reduce to a low simmer for ~{20%minutes}, until tender.

Wash and dry all produce. Meanwhile, halve, peel, and mince the @shallot{1}. Pick the @mint{1/2%ounce} leaves from the stems and thinly slice them, reserving a few for garnish. Coarsely chop the @almonds{1%ounce}. Thinly slice the @dried figs{3%ounce}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine the shallot, @sherry vinegar{2%tablespoon}, @honey{1%teaspoon}, and a large pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Whisk in about @olive oil{2%tablespoon}.

Once the quinoa is done, transfer to a #baking sheet{} or #large bowl{}. Place in the #freezer{} ~{3-5%minutes} to cool slightly.

Toss the cooled quinoa into the vinaigrette along with the almonds, mint and @arugula{2%ounce}. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Serve: Divide the quinoa salad between plates. Top with the figs, @feta cheese{1/2%cup}, and reserved mint leaves. Enjoy!